reviewText: Minimalist platformer/rhythm game. Reminds me of some of the good stuff that came out of Newgrounds back in the day, but smoother and with better production values. I've only beaten the first world so far but the challenge is already ramping up with new obstacles and mechanics. Levels are short with collectibles for replayability and there looks to be quite a lot of levels. If you're into simple but challenging games, I'd say it's worth a play.

reviewText:
Product received for free

Recommended, but with an asterisk.

This game is frustrating, annoying, and extremely satisfying to finally beat. It has a learning curve like a brick wall, mostly due to the single-button controls. Although the level design is quite clever, because of the fast pace of your gooey avatar and close perspective, almost every level feels like a horrible trap designed to ruin your day. Oddly enough, the best levels in the game are the very first and very last ones; they really feel like an effective tutorial and a final exam, respectively.

Speedrunning this game is a nightmare, and going for 100% completion is an exercise in masochism. Play this game for a weird challenge, but maybe don't play it for fun. Or, play it for fun, but never expect to beat it.

OH RIGHT ALSO BE SURE TO SWITCH TO MANUAL WALLJUMPS ASAP. If you don't, you're likely to have a bad time.

reviewText:
Product received for free

Cheery colors?  Bright, giant buttons?  Kids, we're dealing with a mobile game!

Spunk and Moxie is a one-button platformer where you play as either Spunk or Moxie and play your way through many colorful and crazy levels.  Along the way you pick up different kinds of powerups, such as rocket fuel to boost you around, face common dangers, like hacksaws, and learn about the true strength of friendship.  Aww.
There really isn't much to say about the game.  As said before it is a port of a mobile game and probably was put on steam to boost sales.  There isn't anything wrong about the game, it's one of the better one-button games I've seen in a long time, it's just it is out of place on this platform.  That being said I had a blast playing it.  Very simple, yet fun and addictive, the perfect mobile combo.
